@startuml UC-14_Activity
title UC-14: Third-Party App Integration (OAuth)
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FCE4EC
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #C2185B
skinparam ArrowColor #C2185B

start
:Workflow contains third-party integration node;
:Load workflow for execution;
:Detect integration node (Google, Slack, LinkedIn, etc.);
:Retrieve stored credentials for service:
    • Query credentials database
    • Filter by user_id + service
    • Decrypt credential value;
if (Credentials valid?) then (Yes)
    :Build API request:
        • Get endpoint URL
        • Construct headers (auth headers)
        • Format request body
        • Apply parameter mapping;
    :Validate request format:
        • Check required fields
        • Validate data types
        • Apply request schema;
    if (Request valid?) then (Yes)
        :Send API request to third-party service;
        :Set request timeout (30s);
        :Monitor response:
            • Check HTTP status code
            • Parse response body
            • Handle rate limiting;
        if (Rate limit detected?) then (Yes)
            :Calculate backoff delay;
            :Wait before retry;
            :Retry request;
        endif
        if (Response successful?) then (Yes, 200-299)
            :Parse response data;
            :Transform response:
                • Map fields to workflow variables
                • Apply data transformation
                • Validate output schema;
            :Store response in execution context;
            :Continue to next node;
        else (Error)
            :Log API error:
                • Status code
                • Error message
                • Response body;
            :Apply error handling strategy (retry/skip/abort);
        endif
    else (Invalid)
        :Log validation error;
        :Halt workflow with error;
    endif
else (Invalid credentials)
    :Log credential error;
    :Alert user:
        "Credential expired or invalid
        Please update credentials";
    :Abort workflow;
endif
:Log API interaction for audit:
    • API endpoint
    • Request timestamp
    • Response time
    • Status
    • Data transferred;
stop
@enduml
